RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 18100. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs. Preference to horses with the most starts at Penn National since May 31st 2022. (If deemed in advisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs.) (Rail at 14 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HARBOR OF GOLD stalked the pace two deep early on, moved up along the inside through the far turn, slipped through along the rail into the upper stretch and finished well to edge clear under steady pressure. ONE TRUTH was quick to begin to set the early pace, raced just off the inside in the stretch and kept on gamely to the wire. ON THE CHILL prompt the early leader two deep from the outside and weakened a bit the final eighth of a mile. SIR STEELE dropped back off the early pace setters, raced three to four wide in the lane and lacked a rally. GOOD FORTUNE coaxed along from the inside and lacked a bid. HE'S SO FUNNY was void of speed and trailed.

ENTRY.NAME: Good Fortune
ENTRY.OWNER: Sweigart Dennis Schwalm Randy A and Beattie Todd M

ENTRY.NAME: Harbor of Gold
ENTRY.COMMENT: staked 2p, rail upper stretch, drove clear

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27100. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NORMANDY LIFE showed good early foot to set the early pace near the inside down the backstretch, raced well off the inside in the stretch, edged away through the upper stretch under a steady hand ride and was geared down late to race in hand. MEXICAN SUGAR pressed the early leader racing three deep into the far turn and was match for the winner while racing near the rail in the drive. TIME OF OUR LIVES coaxed along early, raced near the inside past the three eighths pole, angled four to five wide into the upper stretch and was no match for the top pair to race along for third. WILD CREATION was coaxed along from the inside, continued an inside into the upper stretch and weakened in the drive. QUEEN OF HEARTS dropped back early, saved ground and never threatened.

ENTRY.NAME: Time of Our Lives
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside 3/8, 4-5 wide upper stretch, along for 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Normandy Life
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace inside, off rail stretch, hand ride, in hand late

ENTRY.NAME: Mexican Sugar
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed 3 path, no match, inside lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 3 1 1/16M Turf CR: 76. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 18000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $16,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000 AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since June 28 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) Preference to horses with the most starts at Penn National since May 31st 20 22. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Sixteenth.) (Rail at 14 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BABKA showed good early foot from the inside to set the early pace and held gamely in the drive to remain clear under strong handling. HUSHEMUP was unhurried early on, raced near the inside past the three eighths pole, raced five wide in the drive and closed in belatedly racing five deep. KAZ MUSIC stalked the pace along the inside, raced two deep in the lane and kept on to the wire. WILL OR WON'T settled off the early going, moved up four wide near the quarter pole and moved up while racing from the outside. BRING THE MAGIC settled off the early going, moved up four wide into the upper stretch and had no final winning bid in the drive. BOHEMIA BABE tracked the early leader two deep and faded. PROPER GRAMMAR stalked the pace along the inside and weakened in the drive. BO RUNKLE reared at the break and trailed.

ENTRY.NAME: Bring the Magic
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled off pace, 4wd upper stretch, no final bid

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 13600. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JANUARY 28. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 28 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MELODIOUS SINGER prompt the early leader two deep and kicked clear through the upper stretch under a steady hand ride. ISABELLA SMILE settled off the early going, raced near the inside past the quarter pole, angled out and got up for the place position. SMOOTH AS GLASS rated along the inside under a firm hold and raced even late with no closing run. UNO TIGRESS showed good early foot along the inside and faltered in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Smooth as Glass
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated inside, firm hold, even late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 10800. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JANUARY 28. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 28 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AGAINST THE ODDS stalked the pace, raced along the inside near the three eighths pole, slipped through the along the rail into the upper stretch and finished well to prove best under steady pressure. REFUND RIGLER dueled for the early lead along the inside, raced just off the inside in the stretch and gave way to winner grudgingly. LAST MINUTE MARIO dueled two deep outside of rival, was in aim inside the eighth pole racing four deep and was outkicked to the wire. MYSTIC POINT stalked the pace, moved up four to five wide around the far turn and flattened out in the drive. CALCULATED THINKIN settled off the early going, raced from the far outside in the lane and had no late rally. KING'S HOUSE was off slowly and lacked a bid.

ENTRY.NAME: Mystic Point
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, 4-5 wide turn, flattened out,

ENTRY.NAME: Calculated Thinkin
ENTRY.OWNER: Turn it Up a Notch Racing

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 10000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JANUARY 28. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TURNPIKE BOB vied for the early lead along the inside, dug in late and prevailed under all out pressure. BEE BY THE SEA stalked the pace, moved up three to five wide around the far turn, surged late from the outside and just missed in a game effort. JETTIN OUT settled off the early pace, moved up three wide in the stretch and finished gamely to the wire. R GOODTIME CHARLIE pressed two deep and weakened the final eighth of a mile. WOLFINBARGER chased the early pace, made a three wide bid near the three eighths pole and weakened in the drive. SHOWER THE PEOPLE slow early on, raced near the inside around the far turn through the stretch and lacked a bid. LAVERY was off a step slow, raced five wide near the three sixteenths pole and never threatened.

ENTRY.NAME: Turnpike Bob
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, dug in late, driving,

ENTRY.NAME: Bee by the Sea
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, 3-5 wide turn, surged, missed

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 15400. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 28 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since May 28 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $10,0 00, if for $9,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MORGANS COVE raced off the early pace, moved up three wide near the three eighths pole, split rivals two deep nearing the sixteenth pole and got up under strong pressure. NEWSDLEY showed good early speed to set the early pace, dug in in late and missed in a game effort. ARROGANTE stalked the pace from the outside, raced three to four wide between in the drive and finished willingly to the wire. SONG SAVER was unhurried early on, moved up five wide near the quarter pole, took aim inside three sixteenths pole and flattened out late while racing from the outside. DESI'S REWARD stalked the pace along the inside down the backstretch, angled to the outside to race from the outside in the stretch and moved up to improve position. NANA'S BOOPA dropped back early and failed to respond. HOP TO A DECISION was void of early speed, raced from the outside in the lane and never threatened. TRUE QUEEN tracked the early leader two deep and tired readily.

ENTRY.NAME: Nana's Boopa
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, failed to respond,

ENTRY.NAME: Song Saver
ENTRY.OWNER: Pewter Stable and Shooting Star Stable (Anspach)
